WEBVTT

00:08.429 --> 00:11.802
Meredith: As surgeons,
we are our brothers' keepers.

00:11.802 --> 00:13.594
Ride or die.

00:13.594 --> 00:14.895
Womb to tomb.

00:19.560 --> 00:21.142
[ Exhales sharply ]

00:21.142 --> 00:24.525
♪♪

00:24.525 --> 00:26.607
We see each other's fears.

00:26.607 --> 00:28.859
We see the white-knuckled panic
of failure.

00:32.493 --> 00:34.615
We see ourselves.

00:34.615 --> 00:37.248
And who the hell
likes looking at that?

00:37.248 --> 00:40.161
Alex, we should...
get going.

00:40.161 --> 00:41.752
That's the wrong tie.

00:44.255 --> 00:46.217
Well, it's not
gonna really matter

00:46.217 --> 00:47.668
what tie I'm wearing
when, uh...

00:47.668 --> 00:49.630
Did I tell you I have
a thymectomy today?

00:49.630 --> 00:51.972
Patient has myasthenia
without a thymoma,

00:51.972 --> 00:54.935
so I'm thinking I can get away
with a partial sternotomy.

00:54.935 --> 00:57.348
So, we're avoiding what's
actually gonna happen today.

00:57.348 --> 00:59.140
We're discussing medicine.

00:59.140 --> 01:01.812
We're doing our rounds.
Surgery and work.

01:01.812 --> 01:03.984
That's what's going to
get us through today.

01:07.818 --> 01:10.281
[ Siren wails ]

01:10.281 --> 01:11.652
I don't spy
on my co-workers.

01:11.652 --> 01:13.694
I'm not asking you to spy
on your co-workers.

01:13.694 --> 01:16.287
No, you're asking me
to be your mole.

01:16.287 --> 01:18.999
I'm asking you to keep
this hospital safe.

01:18.999 --> 01:21.202
This Karev-DeLuca thing
is a mess.

01:21.202 --> 01:24.415
I have an attending who posted
bail for another attending,

01:24.415 --> 01:26.086
an intern
pressing charges.

01:26.086 --> 01:27.588
People are taking sides.

01:27.588 --> 01:28.839
I'm trying
to hold us down,

01:28.839 --> 01:30.711
but I need someone
to be my eyes and ears.

01:30.711 --> 01:33.384
Baby, baby, I'm just starting
to get my reputation back.

01:33.384 --> 01:34.635
Just my eyes and ears.

01:34.635 --> 01:36.267
No!

01:36.267 --> 01:38.679
When Webber was Chief,
I was his eyes and ears.

01:38.679 --> 01:41.812
Okay, but, Chief, Chief,
you can have my whole body --

01:41.812 --> 01:43.354
Don't be nasty.

01:43.354 --> 01:45.226
But not my eyes and ears.
I'm not your mole.

01:45.226 --> 01:46.487
[ Groans ]

01:48.779 --> 01:50.361
You're right.
Hm?

01:50.361 --> 01:52.823
I know.
What am I right about this time?

01:52.823 --> 01:54.785
Okay.
You need eyes and ears.

01:54.785 --> 01:56.237
I could be your mole.

01:56.237 --> 01:57.738
[ Scoffs ]
Won't work.

01:57.738 --> 01:59.660
People shut up
when you're around.

01:59.660 --> 02:02.203
If they know I'm around.

02:02.203 --> 02:04.915
Have you heard
of Hercules Mulligan?

02:04.915 --> 02:06.547
He was a great
Revolutionary War spy,

02:06.547 --> 02:07.748
helped defeat the British.

02:07.748 --> 02:09.340
No one
saw him coming or going.

02:09.340 --> 02:11.382
I know
who Hercules Mulligan was,

02:11.382 --> 02:14.845
and you're no Hercul--

02:14.845 --> 02:18.058
Hm, well, damn.

02:18.058 --> 02:20.601
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:26.267 --> 02:28.229
Hey, I thought you had
Alex's thing this morning.

02:28.229 --> 02:29.980
Uh, we do.
We are keeping our heads up.

02:29.980 --> 02:31.362
We are working.

02:31.362 --> 02:33.234
-It happened again last night.
-Again?

02:33.234 --> 02:34.575
Riggs walked me to my car.

02:34.575 --> 02:36.327
And we said good night,

02:36.327 --> 02:40.451
and then he took me
in the parking lot...

02:40.451 --> 02:43.043
over and over again.

02:43.043 --> 02:45.085
That's the third time
this week.

02:45.085 --> 02:47.548
Mer, these dreams
are really hot.

02:47.548 --> 02:49.840
In the parking lot?
No.

02:49.840 --> 02:51.882
I should
just ask him out.
Here you go, Doctor.

02:51.882 --> 02:53.214
Thanks.
I know.
I'm his boss.

02:53.214 --> 02:54.925
What if I ask him
and he says no,

02:54.925 --> 02:56.927
or it comes off like
some gross sexual harassment?

02:56.927 --> 02:59.720
Which is the only kind of
sexual harassment.

02:59.720 --> 03:01.432
But what
if I don't ask him?

03:01.432 --> 03:04.184
Am I just gonna wait around
for my life to happen?

03:04.184 --> 03:07.017
Just wait for my big love?
You've had yours.

03:07.017 --> 03:08.859
Amelia has hers.
I want mine.

03:08.859 --> 03:11.692
So I am acting
like a grown-ass woman,

03:11.692 --> 03:15.075
and I am asking him out?

03:15.075 --> 03:16.697
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Was that a question mark?

03:16.697 --> 03:18.409
No.

03:18.409 --> 03:21.031
Unless you think that
it should be a question mark.

03:22.663 --> 03:25.125
This is happening.
I'm doing this.

03:25.125 --> 03:26.287
This is
definitely happening.

03:28.419 --> 03:29.750
Good talk.

03:29.750 --> 03:31.382
[ Elevator bell dings ]

03:31.382 --> 03:33.674
And the wedding photographer
wants us to pick our favorites.

03:33.674 --> 03:35.716
Wait, from 500 proofs?
We have jobs.

03:35.716 --> 03:37.468
We are very, very busy.

03:37.468 --> 03:39.219
So busy all the time

03:39.219 --> 03:41.011
Ooh. Oh.

03:41.011 --> 03:43.183
-[ Clears throat ] Hey.
-Morning, Riggs.

03:43.183 --> 03:44.475
-Morning.
-Morning, guys.

03:44.475 --> 03:45.556
Oh, I almost forgot.

03:45.556 --> 03:48.188
You want me
to bring anything tonight?

03:48.188 --> 03:50.401
I make a whitebait fritter
that's out of this world.

03:54.525 --> 03:55.856
You invited Riggs
to our house?

03:55.856 --> 03:57.117
We have a new home.

03:57.117 --> 03:59.450
We're supposed to have
friends and family over

03:59.450 --> 04:01.071
to warm it up, right?

04:01.071 --> 04:02.863
Wait. This is a housewarming?
Who else did you invite?

04:02.863 --> 04:05.416
You two were so happy
at the wedding,

04:05.416 --> 04:07.037
and you were
so close once.

04:07.037 --> 04:08.369
That was a long time ago.

04:08.369 --> 04:09.750
You should have checked
with me first.

04:09.750 --> 04:10.921
Sorry. You're right.
I meant to.

04:10.921 --> 04:12.873
[ Sighs ]

04:12.873 --> 04:14.795
You were never gonna check in
with me, were you?

04:14.795 --> 04:17.047
-Probably not.
-Hm.

04:17.047 --> 04:18.799
Dr. Shepherd,
how's it going?

04:18.799 --> 04:19.840
I suck at marriage.

04:19.840 --> 04:22.012
I'm sorry.
I need a favor.

04:22.012 --> 04:23.724
Can you take Wilson
on your service today?

04:23.724 --> 04:25.556
No, I have Warren,

04:25.556 --> 04:27.187
and he's already familiar
with my Wilma case.

04:27.187 --> 04:28.439
You know
how gnarly she's gonna be.

04:28.439 --> 04:29.770
But if you put Wilson
on your service,

04:29.770 --> 04:31.021
she doesn't have to work
with Karev.

04:31.021 --> 04:32.893
I see
you've picked a side.

04:32.893 --> 04:34.605
I'm on the side of

04:34.605 --> 04:36.487
"We all want to punch interns,
but we resist."

04:36.487 --> 04:37.738
So, Wilson gets neuro.

04:37.738 --> 04:39.360
What do you get out of it?
A surgery? What?

04:39.360 --> 04:41.902
Nothing.
Just trying to be a good friend.

04:41.902 --> 04:43.494
That's all.
Please.

04:45.406 --> 04:47.458
-I'll take Wilson.
-Thank you.

04:47.458 --> 04:51.332
Oh, and can you take
pictures of Wilma?

04:51.332 --> 04:53.414
-I want neuro porn.
-[ Chuckles ]

04:56.917 --> 04:59.380
Ben: Dr. Karev,
this is Zach Thompson.

04:59.380 --> 05:01.011
Six months
post-renal transplant,

05:01.011 --> 05:02.343
complaining
of abdominal pain.

05:02.343 --> 05:04.224
I know the history.

05:04.224 --> 05:05.766
-Dr. Alex.
-Hey, buddy.

05:05.766 --> 05:07.518
Hey, Reena.

05:07.518 --> 05:09.269
I didn't want to see you guys
here again.
Yeah.

05:12.142 --> 05:13.604
When did the pain start?

05:13.604 --> 05:15.936
This morning.
It came on kind of gradually.

05:15.936 --> 05:17.147
I got scared.

05:17.147 --> 05:19.029
His kidney is so new,
and I worry.

05:19.029 --> 05:20.200
Ow.

05:20.200 --> 05:21.532
-Ow!
-Sorry, bud.

05:21.532 --> 05:23.444
No, I'm fine.

05:23.444 --> 05:26.116
Don't make me
give my kidney back.

05:26.116 --> 05:27.327
[ Sighs ] Well, look,

05:27.327 --> 05:29.039
I'm gonna have to run
a few tests,

05:29.039 --> 05:30.661
and I need you
to be brave.

05:30.661 --> 05:32.503
But remember what we say?

05:32.503 --> 05:35.546
No matter how bad it gets,
no matter how scary...

05:35.546 --> 05:36.797
Nothing's as bad
as broccoli.

05:36.797 --> 05:38.419
...nothing's as bad
as broccoli.

05:40.801 --> 05:43.424
Here's our girl.

05:43.424 --> 05:45.846
Hi, sweetie.
Gimme, gimme, gimme.

05:45.846 --> 05:47.638
Harriet is gaining weight
right on schedule.

05:47.638 --> 05:50.561
-She's healthy and fat.
-Fat baby.

05:50.561 --> 05:52.523
Fat baby. And healthy enough
to go home today.

05:52.523 --> 05:53.564
Yeah?

05:54.735 --> 05:55.936
Are you sure she's ready?

05:55.936 --> 05:57.187
What about her respirations?
I thought I --

05:57.187 --> 05:58.899
Kepner, you can take
your kid home.

05:58.899 --> 06:00.611
[ Cellphone chimes ]

06:00.611 --> 06:02.443
[ Baby cooing ]
Yeah, I know.

06:02.443 --> 06:05.696
-Oh, yeah.
-Look, I got to go.

06:05.696 --> 06:07.037
Oh, that's today.

06:07.037 --> 06:08.909
Congrats on the fat baby.

06:08.909 --> 06:10.451
Okay, yeah, thanks.

06:10.451 --> 06:12.042
[ Baby coos ]

06:12.042 --> 06:14.495
Why the face?
It's a good thing.

06:14.495 --> 06:15.586
Not for me.

06:15.586 --> 06:17.207
What do you mean?

06:17.207 --> 06:20.210
My incision opened back up.
They want to do wound therapy.

06:20.210 --> 06:21.962
Ah.

06:21.962 --> 06:24.505
Harriet's going home.

06:24.505 --> 06:26.386
But I'm not.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.929
[ Cooing ]

06:30.310 --> 06:32.643
Meredith: So, they're just
charging you today.

06:32.643 --> 06:34.224
I know.

06:34.224 --> 06:35.856
It'll probably be a misdemeanor
with probation.

06:35.856 --> 06:37.017
I know, Mer.

06:37.017 --> 06:39.399
Is the State ready to charge?

06:39.399 --> 06:40.691
We are, Your Honor.

06:40.691 --> 06:42.362
We're seeking felony assault
in the second degree.

06:43.484 --> 06:45.826
Felony?
This must be a mistake.

06:45.826 --> 06:47.027
It's not, Your Honor.

06:47.027 --> 06:48.489
What the hell?
I thought --

06:48.489 --> 06:49.790
The State is pulling this
at the last minute.

06:49.790 --> 06:51.622
It's called
prosecutorial discretion.

06:51.622 --> 06:53.454
It's overreaching.

06:53.454 --> 06:55.666
-It's not, Your Honor.
-This is a misdemeanor case.

06:55.666 --> 06:57.538
Tell that to the victim
seated here in the courtroom --

06:57.538 --> 07:00.130
a first-year surgical intern
who almost lost his career

07:00.130 --> 07:02.673
when the defendant,
his professional superior,

07:02.673 --> 07:05.345
his teacher,
was unable to mask his rage.

07:05.345 --> 07:08.469
This act was a felony.

07:08.469 --> 07:10.310
The State and Dr. DeLuca

07:10.310 --> 07:12.933
want the appropriate
justice here.

07:12.933 --> 07:15.556
You want to argue this now?
Fine.

07:15.556 --> 07:17.858
The defendant is a pediatric
surgeon with no priors.

07:17.858 --> 07:19.019
-He --
-We're not at trial.

07:19.019 --> 07:21.321
We're here to enter a plea
to the charge.

07:21.321 --> 07:24.154
And the charge is felony assault
in the second degree.

07:24.154 --> 07:25.866
How do you plead, Dr. Karev?

07:26.907 --> 07:29.029
How do you plead, Dr. Karev?

07:29.029 --> 07:30.450
You have to answer.

07:30.450 --> 07:31.832
Not guilty.

07:33.624 --> 07:36.456
[ Birds calling ]

07:36.456 --> 07:38.288
This is just a charge.

07:38.288 --> 07:40.210
Yeah, a felony charge.

07:40.210 --> 07:42.503
But you haven't been convicted
of anything.

07:42.503 --> 07:44.464
Alex.
Every single one.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.926
Every guy I grew up with

07:45.926 --> 07:48.639
is either right where I left
him, dead, or in prison.

07:50.641 --> 07:52.553
I thought I was special
'cause I went to med school.

07:52.553 --> 07:55.936
Guess you can't wash
the stink off trash.

07:55.936 --> 07:57.558
You're not trash.

07:57.558 --> 08:00.150
You're a surgeon,
and you are not going to prison.

08:00.150 --> 08:02.903
-You don't know that.
-You are not going to prison.

08:36.767 --> 08:39.099
Do you know the charge?

08:39.099 --> 08:41.101
Yes.

08:41.101 --> 08:43.483
The D.A. subpoenaed
DeLuca's medical records

08:43.483 --> 08:45.105
and your personnel file.

08:45.105 --> 08:46.146
What now?

08:46.146 --> 08:48.028
What now?

08:48.028 --> 08:50.781
What now?

08:50.781 --> 08:52.492
[ Sighs ]

08:54.114 --> 08:55.746
You know, people come
to this hospital

08:55.746 --> 08:57.868
so that we can help them.

08:57.868 --> 09:02.082
Do you know how many problems
I have to deal with already?

09:02.082 --> 09:05.465
Who gets the expensive
experimental drug?

09:05.465 --> 09:08.378
Whose body deserves
the organ transplant?

09:08.378 --> 09:10.550
Which parent is ready
to hear that,

09:10.550 --> 09:12.803
"Yes,
your toddler is dead,

09:12.803 --> 09:15.055
but here is a bill

09:15.055 --> 09:16.346
for a quarter million dollars
anyway."

09:16.346 --> 09:17.678
Problems!

09:17.678 --> 09:19.940
Real problems, Karev.

09:19.940 --> 09:23.734
Yet somehow you are
now problem number one.

09:23.734 --> 09:27.608
A pediatric surgeon
walking around this hospital

09:27.608 --> 09:29.449
with an assault charge.

09:29.449 --> 09:32.192
Do you realize what happens if
you're convicted of a felony?!

09:34.364 --> 09:36.617
Yes, Dr. Bailey,
I realize.

09:39.499 --> 09:41.291
Well, do you have
a decent lawyer?

09:41.291 --> 09:43.624
Do you need help or...

09:43.624 --> 09:45.585
Are we done?

09:47.417 --> 09:50.130
DeLuca's starting back today.
Is there gonna be a problem?

09:50.130 --> 09:53.093
Not from me.

09:53.093 --> 09:54.594
Then we're done.

09:56.637 --> 09:58.979
[ Door opens, closes ]

10:02.062 --> 10:03.483
When you get home,

10:03.483 --> 10:05.435
just put her in
the little yellow onesie

10:05.435 --> 10:07.187
with the frogs on it.

10:07.187 --> 10:09.900
[ Voice breaking ]
That was her going home
from the hospital onesie.

10:09.900 --> 10:12.032
I know.
I'll take pictures.

10:13.193 --> 10:15.195
[ Sobbing ]

10:15.195 --> 10:16.697
Hey.

10:16.697 --> 10:19.039
She's going home
without me.

10:19.039 --> 10:20.500
Yeah.

10:20.500 --> 10:22.162
And what did we just say
about that?

10:22.162 --> 10:25.205
The important thing is that
she's healthy and I'm healthy.

10:25.205 --> 10:26.206
Exactly.

10:26.206 --> 10:27.337
That's crap!

10:28.508 --> 10:30.170
She's supposed to be
with me --

10:30.170 --> 10:32.843
bonding and attaching
or whatever.

10:32.843 --> 10:35.465
Smelling me
like birds and dogs.

10:35.465 --> 10:36.516
Birds and dogs?

10:36.516 --> 10:38.679
Shut up. It's nature.

10:38.679 --> 10:43.023
How's she gonna attach to me
when she's there and I'm here?

10:43.023 --> 10:44.434
You're gonna
be discharged soon.

10:44.434 --> 10:48.148
And then what?
I'm still gonna be in recovery.

10:48.148 --> 10:50.110
You know the ins and outs
of post-op incisions.

10:50.110 --> 10:54.614
I'm not even gonna be able to
pick her up with-- without help.

10:54.614 --> 10:58.078
I'm gonna have to hire someone
to come and take care of her,

10:58.078 --> 11:03.623
some mama bird who smells good
and bonds with my baby

11:03.623 --> 11:06.166
while I just lie there
and watch.

11:06.166 --> 11:07.667
You know what?
You should just go.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.710
I'm not going anywhere
while you're this upset.

11:09.710 --> 11:12.172
You have to
because I'm not gonna stop.

11:12.172 --> 11:13.924
I'm just gonna die
of dehydration.
Shh, shh.

11:13.924 --> 11:15.465
It's gonna be all right,
you know.
Get out.

11:20.761 --> 11:22.933
[ Sobs ]

11:26.937 --> 11:30.190
Dr. Karev, uh,
I've got Zach's labs.

11:30.190 --> 11:33.193
His CRP is a little elevated,
but, um...

11:33.193 --> 11:34.905
-Dr. Karev?
-Hm, what?

11:34.905 --> 11:37.027
I just didn't know
if you heard me.

11:37.027 --> 11:39.239
Uh, just, uh, tell me
what the C.T. showed.

11:39.239 --> 11:40.660
Well,
his kidney looks good,

11:40.660 --> 11:42.372
but he is showing signs
of early appendicitis.

11:42.372 --> 11:44.084
What?

11:44.084 --> 11:45.786
Appendicitis?
So he needs another surgery?

11:45.786 --> 11:47.537
Well,
I want to avoid that.

11:47.537 --> 11:49.960
The immunosuppressants he's on
because of the transplant

11:49.960 --> 11:52.252
put him at greater risk
for post-op infections.

11:52.252 --> 11:54.174
I want to start him on
broad-spectrum antibiotics,

11:54.174 --> 11:55.465
see if it clears up
on its own.

11:55.465 --> 11:56.757
Okay.

11:56.757 --> 11:58.218
I'll be by to check on him
every hour.

11:58.218 --> 11:59.599
Thank you.

11:59.599 --> 12:01.051
Which means you and I
are gonna be here

12:01.051 --> 12:02.342
hanging out all day.

12:02.342 --> 12:05.345
I bet I can score a video game
for your room, deal?

12:05.345 --> 12:07.347
Deal.

12:11.852 --> 12:14.614
So, uh,
how's Alex holding up?

12:14.614 --> 12:16.196
He's working.
I'm working.

12:16.196 --> 12:17.778
We're focused on medicine.

12:17.778 --> 12:20.320
Right, yes, good.
We should all focus on medicine.

12:20.320 --> 12:22.863
Lap pads.

12:22.863 --> 12:25.365
Just -- How should
I ask Riggs out?

12:25.365 --> 12:26.746
Is there a way to do it

12:26.746 --> 12:28.919
so that the boss thing
isn't a thing?

12:28.919 --> 12:31.832
Oh, you actually meant that.
You're ask gonna Riggs out?

12:31.832 --> 12:33.964
Grey, what are
you doing tonight?

12:33.964 --> 12:35.135
Nothing.

12:35.135 --> 12:37.968
Uh, Amelia invited Riggs
to dinner at our house.

12:37.968 --> 12:40.010
She's trying to make us --
I don't know -- friends again.

12:40.010 --> 12:41.091
[ Chuckles ]

12:41.091 --> 12:42.722
I need you to come over
and talk to him

12:42.722 --> 12:43.513
so I don't have to.

12:43.513 --> 12:45.645
-I'm busy.
-Wh--

12:45.645 --> 12:47.978
Come on. You guys got along
at the wedding.

12:47.978 --> 12:49.349
It was a wedding.
I had tequila.

12:49.349 --> 12:51.651
You need a buffer?
I can buffer.

12:51.651 --> 12:52.983
-I'm a great buffer.
-You're free?

12:52.983 --> 12:54.774
Tonight's perfect.
What time?

12:54.774 --> 12:56.236
8:00-ish?

12:56.236 --> 12:58.158
Uh, awesome,
I'll be there.

12:58.158 --> 13:00.160
We'll see you at 8:00.

13:00.160 --> 13:01.741
Yeah.

13:01.741 --> 13:03.113
Hey, you changed your mind.

13:03.113 --> 13:04.995
If you're going,
I'll go.

13:07.457 --> 13:09.619
Dr. Shepherd.

13:09.619 --> 13:10.831
I-I just want to say
thank you

13:10.831 --> 13:12.082
for letting me work
on your service.

13:12.082 --> 13:13.173
I know that you --

13:13.173 --> 13:14.584
Stop thanking me.
We got work to do.

13:14.584 --> 13:15.836
Wilma is waiting.

13:15.836 --> 13:16.877
Wilma?

13:16.877 --> 13:18.508
Nasty, annoying Wilma.

13:18.508 --> 13:20.130
It says here Patricia.

13:20.130 --> 13:22.923
Hello.
So, how we doing?

13:22.923 --> 13:24.474
I'm fine.

13:24.474 --> 13:25.595
[ Whispering ]
It's not Wilma.

13:25.595 --> 13:27.017
So, you know the drill.

13:27.017 --> 13:28.348
We are going to draw
a few more labs,

13:28.348 --> 13:29.729
do a pre-op C.T.,

13:29.729 --> 13:32.312
and tomorrow,
it is all about Wilma.

13:32.312 --> 13:33.813
It's Patricia.
Patricia.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.896
Oh, she's talking about
the tumor, dear.

13:35.896 --> 13:39.199
I'm Patricia.
The tumor is Wilma.

13:39.199 --> 13:42.532
She named her tumor
after her ex-husband's mistress.

13:42.532 --> 13:44.114
Wilma --
because they're both

13:44.114 --> 13:47.157
parasitic mounds
of unwanted flesh.

13:47.157 --> 13:48.949
And tomorrow,
we are kicking Wilma's ass.

13:48.949 --> 13:50.911
Yeah,
that bitch is going down.

13:50.911 --> 13:52.162
-Mm-hmm.
-[ Grunts ]

13:54.334 --> 13:56.836
Wilson, meet Wilma.

13:56.836 --> 14:00.050
Tomorrow, we beat the crap
out of this bitch.

14:00.050 --> 14:02.422
[ Sighs ]

14:02.422 --> 14:04.224
Come on.
Show some enthusiasm.

14:04.224 --> 14:05.385
I'm enthusiastic.

14:05.385 --> 14:08.018
It's just that the tumor is
a woman named Wilma.

14:08.018 --> 14:10.020
So?

14:10.020 --> 14:12.602
And you're excited
to kick Wilma's ass

14:12.602 --> 14:14.104
and beat the crap
out of Wilma.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.236
And it's cute when it's the name
of a tumor.

14:16.236 --> 14:18.318
It's just that when it's the
name of a woman, it's -- it's --

14:18.318 --> 14:19.529
It's what?

14:21.031 --> 14:22.862
It's nothing.
It's nothing.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.864
[ Beeping ]

14:24.864 --> 14:26.536
The Karev thing --
I'm an idiot.

14:26.536 --> 14:28.788
Here I am,
saying all these violent things

14:28.788 --> 14:29.869
after what
you've been through.

14:29.869 --> 14:31.871
What I've been through?

14:31.871 --> 14:33.954
Witnessing Karev
attack DeLuca.

14:33.954 --> 14:35.835
I'm sorry.
I'm bringing up bad memories.

14:35.835 --> 14:37.757
You must think
I am the worst person.

14:37.757 --> 14:40.260
It's -- It's okay.
I'm fine.

14:40.260 --> 14:41.381
Are you?

14:43.093 --> 14:46.346
I don't have
any place to live.

14:46.346 --> 14:49.469
And the entire hospital
won't stop whispering

14:49.469 --> 14:51.271
about the scarlet letter
on my chest.

14:51.271 --> 14:54.604
So it just feels like
I'm trapped in a glass box

14:54.604 --> 14:57.777
and everyone's on the outside
watching while I run out of air.

14:57.777 --> 15:00.190
But, yeah,
it's [chuckles]

15:00.190 --> 15:01.611
I'm great.

15:01.611 --> 15:03.483
Okay.

15:03.483 --> 15:06.866
I'm having a housewarming party,
and you are coming.

15:06.866 --> 15:09.289
You need a break
from your life.

15:09.289 --> 15:10.700
Alex will not be there.

15:10.700 --> 15:14.124
I just picked a side,
and I'm on yours.

15:17.337 --> 15:19.799
[ Cash register beeps ]

15:19.799 --> 15:22.172
It's been quite a day.

15:22.172 --> 15:23.923
Dr. Webber.

15:23.923 --> 15:28.008
They're have been rumblings
about some sort of turf war

15:28.008 --> 15:30.680
over who gets control
of Dr. Torres' ortho lab

15:30.680 --> 15:31.972
now that she's gone.

15:31.972 --> 15:34.514
Oh, and, uh, doctors
at the Duquette Clinic,

15:34.514 --> 15:36.726
they feel overworked.

15:36.726 --> 15:39.059
-At the clinic?
-Mm.

15:39.059 --> 15:40.730
That's not news.

15:40.730 --> 15:41.982
-Hm?
-You know what's news?

15:41.982 --> 15:44.694
Karev was charged
with a felony.

15:44.694 --> 15:45.825
Mm.

15:45.825 --> 15:46.866
[ Bites apple ]

15:46.866 --> 15:47.777
I did not hear that.

15:51.661 --> 15:53.573
[ Elevator bell dings ]

16:05.425 --> 16:06.926
First day back?

16:06.926 --> 16:08.138
Mm-hmm.

16:08.138 --> 16:10.260
How is it?

16:10.260 --> 16:12.182
It's fine.

16:12.182 --> 16:15.095
DeLuca, I know
I don't know you very well,

16:15.095 --> 16:17.017
but you know
I was attacked.

16:19.149 --> 16:21.021
I remember.

16:25.565 --> 16:30.450
I didn't want to forgive
the guy who attacked me.

16:30.450 --> 16:32.492
But I did
because I needed to.

16:32.492 --> 16:34.114
The guy who attacked you
was in a fugue state.

16:34.114 --> 16:35.665
Dr. Karev knew
what he was doing.

16:35.665 --> 16:37.207
Have you ever made
a horrible mistake

16:37.207 --> 16:38.378
because you overreacted

16:38.378 --> 16:41.291
or you just had
the wrong information?

16:41.291 --> 16:43.883
Dr. Karev
is genuinely sorry

16:43.883 --> 16:45.925
and would like
to tell you himself.

16:45.925 --> 16:47.967
Well, I'm --
I'm not ready for that.

16:47.967 --> 16:49.629
Okay.

16:53.012 --> 16:55.395
Just you are an intern,

16:55.395 --> 16:57.897
and you shouldn't be spending
your time in a courtroom.

16:57.897 --> 17:00.019
You should be scrubbing in
on surgeries.

17:00.019 --> 17:01.401
This job is hard enough.

17:01.401 --> 17:03.523
Just don't need
to make it any harder.

17:03.523 --> 17:04.604
Look, we shouldn't talk about
the case, all right?

17:04.604 --> 17:06.566
Okay, okay.
I'm...

17:09.199 --> 17:11.911
Look, I know
you can keep me out of the O.R.

17:11.911 --> 17:13.453
You can end my career,

17:13.453 --> 17:14.744
and you can ruin my life
if you want to.

17:14.744 --> 17:16.246
I'm not trying
to ruin your life.

17:16.246 --> 17:17.867
You don't get to.

17:17.867 --> 17:19.209
You think
because you're an attending

17:19.209 --> 17:20.790
and Dr. Karev's an attending
you can threaten me?

17:22.792 --> 17:24.834
I don't care.
It's not gonna work.

17:24.834 --> 17:26.506
[ Elevator bell dings ]

17:33.263 --> 17:34.764
[ Babies cooing ]

17:34.764 --> 17:37.137
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:39.389 --> 17:41.771
Okay, so, this is bad.

17:41.771 --> 17:44.184
Well, save it,
'cause I don't need it.

17:44.184 --> 17:46.566
I think I might have
just threatened DeLuca.

17:46.566 --> 17:48.398
What? What?

17:48.398 --> 17:50.069
I was trying to help.

17:50.069 --> 17:50.820
What?!

17:50.820 --> 17:52.362
I didn't mean it.

17:52.362 --> 17:53.533
What did you --
Why would you s--

17:53.533 --> 17:54.904
What exactly did you say?

17:54.904 --> 17:56.116
He twisted my words.

17:56.116 --> 17:58.458
I just got charged
with a felony today.

17:58.458 --> 17:59.789
This is my life, Mer.

17:59.789 --> 18:01.541
Dr. Karev.

18:01.541 --> 18:02.752
I was just looking

18:02.752 --> 18:03.753
at Zach's latest absolute
neutrophil count, and --

18:03.753 --> 18:05.295
I saw it.
It's fine.

18:05.295 --> 18:06.796
Well, his heart rate
is inching up.

18:06.796 --> 18:08.128
I've had him
for three years.

18:08.128 --> 18:09.509
His heart rate rises
every time he comes here.

18:09.509 --> 18:10.970
He's a nervous kid.

18:10.970 --> 18:12.802
But this looks --
I looked at it.
I saw the labs.

18:12.802 --> 18:15.305
I did my job,
now do yours.

18:15.305 --> 18:18.268
I'll keep you posted.

18:18.268 --> 18:19.889
[ Sighs ]

18:19.889 --> 18:21.221
Crap.

18:21.221 --> 18:22.772
You think
DeLuca's gonna say anything?

18:22.772 --> 18:24.774
-I don't know.
-Yeah, he will.

18:24.774 --> 18:27.897
Or he won't.
We can't control it.

18:27.897 --> 18:30.530
All we can do is just go on,
live our lives,

18:30.530 --> 18:32.992
be there for our patients
and our friends,

18:32.992 --> 18:34.494
and go to dinner parties.

18:34.494 --> 18:36.156
I'm not going to a party.

18:36.156 --> 18:38.498
You have to go
because I have to go.

18:38.498 --> 18:40.290
And if I can go to court
for you,

18:40.290 --> 18:42.202
you can go
to a dinner party for me.

18:42.202 --> 18:45.205
8:00.

18:45.205 --> 18:46.956
[ Doorbell rings ]

18:50.750 --> 18:54.254
Sorry, I had an aortic
valvuloplasty and I --

18:54.254 --> 18:55.885
Wilson.

18:55.885 --> 18:57.257
I mean...

18:57.257 --> 18:58.518
Hi, Wilson.

18:58.518 --> 19:01.601
Should've warned you
this is just casual.

19:01.601 --> 19:04.314
What? I'm casual.

19:04.314 --> 19:05.855
[ Door opens ]
I'm casual.
You look hot.

19:05.855 --> 19:06.856
No. I look hot?

19:06.856 --> 19:08.768
Your butt
looks like an apple.

19:08.768 --> 19:12.111
Hey, Pierce,
when did you get here?

19:12.111 --> 19:13.943
Okay. I'm tagging you in.
Riggs is right over there.

19:13.943 --> 19:15.034
-Oh.
-She's your buffer?

19:15.034 --> 19:16.446
No, Maggie,
you are not tagged in.

19:16.446 --> 19:17.737
I'm tagging her in.

19:17.737 --> 19:19.409
That kind of defeats the point
of all of this.

19:19.409 --> 19:20.740
I didn't agree
to all of this.

19:20.740 --> 19:21.831
No, tag me in.
It's fine.

19:21.831 --> 19:23.453
You're starting
a thing here.

19:23.453 --> 19:24.994
No, it's okay.
All good.

19:24.994 --> 19:26.786
And you're not even
giving it a chance.

19:26.786 --> 19:28.248
Guys,
I'll tag myself in.

19:28.248 --> 19:30.089
You obviously
need to talk about this.

19:30.089 --> 19:31.711
And I am right behind you.

19:31.711 --> 19:33.593
-No, you don't have to.
-I don't mind.

19:35.885 --> 19:37.297
Jackson:
You're still crying?

19:37.297 --> 19:39.759
Of course
I'm still crying.

19:39.759 --> 19:41.351
April, come on, okay?

19:41.351 --> 19:43.933
I'm gonna bring her by every
single day at the hospital.

19:43.933 --> 19:45.265
We already talked about it.

19:45.265 --> 19:47.807
As soon as you get home,
we'll fly your mom back out,

19:47.807 --> 19:49.399
get her to stay out here
for a couple months.

19:49.399 --> 19:51.571
My mom already came
for as long as she could, okay?

19:51.571 --> 19:52.942
I can't ask her
to come back out.

19:52.942 --> 19:54.984
She's -- She's got work.

19:54.984 --> 19:56.696
Well,
get a baby nurse

19:56.696 --> 19:58.278
who can stay
and live with you, then.

19:58.278 --> 19:59.869
I can't afford that.

19:59.869 --> 20:01.281
I'm loaded. I can.

20:01.281 --> 20:03.162
Well, I'm not.

20:03.162 --> 20:05.415
And we're not married.

20:05.415 --> 20:06.956
Yes, I know.

20:06.956 --> 20:08.918
You can't fix this, okay?

20:08.918 --> 20:11.881
I have to figure this out.
I am a single mom.

20:11.881 --> 20:16.256
April, I'm her father.
I'm right here.

20:16.256 --> 20:19.549
As long as Harriet is fed
and sleeping and happy,

20:19.549 --> 20:21.431
you're doing your job.

20:21.431 --> 20:24.644
You don't need to, like,
check in on me, okay?

20:24.644 --> 20:27.307
Or call unless
Harriet needs me, okay?

20:27.307 --> 20:28.688
So I'm just supposed to
let you cry, then?

20:28.688 --> 20:30.229
Yes!

20:30.229 --> 20:31.731
Good night, Jackson.

20:31.731 --> 20:34.153
♪ Feelin' like you got the whole
world on your shoulders ♪

20:35.945 --> 20:40.280
♪ Try to walk with it,
but you stumble and fall again ♪

20:40.280 --> 20:41.571
You're here. Good.

20:41.571 --> 20:44.163
He's been with Maggie for
a while, but you're up next.

20:44.163 --> 20:45.865
I had not
put my bag down yet.

20:45.865 --> 20:47.126
If you don't get
in there,

20:47.126 --> 20:48.788
Amelia's gonna
make me talk to him,

20:48.788 --> 20:50.079
and we're
gonna fight about it.

20:50.079 --> 20:51.541
You've been married
for like two minutes.

20:51.541 --> 20:53.082
Right,
so just get in there.

20:53.082 --> 20:54.253
Fine, fine.

20:56.376 --> 20:58.678
Hey, hey.

20:58.678 --> 21:01.260
Hey.
Hey.

21:01.260 --> 21:03.803
Have you had the tour yet?
Owen gives a great tour.

21:03.803 --> 21:05.014
Yeah,
I helped him move in.

21:05.014 --> 21:06.976
We painted the bedroom
since then, so...

21:06.976 --> 21:08.438
Okay.
Nathan, you want to...

21:08.438 --> 21:10.310
Hm.
Oh, actually,
I need to talk to Dr. Riggs

21:10.310 --> 21:12.271
about Mrs., uh, Peterkin.

21:12.271 --> 21:13.693
She relapsed.

21:13.693 --> 21:15.815
Great.
So it's just us, then.

21:15.815 --> 21:18.358
Let's go.
Come on, let's go.

21:20.570 --> 21:23.282
Who's Mrs...Peterkin?

21:23.282 --> 21:24.784
There is no Mrs. Peterkin.

21:24.784 --> 21:27.537
-You just --
-Maggie is going to ask you out.

21:27.537 --> 21:29.078
On a date.

21:29.078 --> 21:30.500
Oh, so...

21:30.500 --> 21:32.211
Maggie wants me?

21:32.211 --> 21:34.083
She wants to date you.

21:34.083 --> 21:37.216
And you are going to be nice
and say no.

21:37.216 --> 21:39.298
Oh, so she doesn't know that
you're madly in love with me.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.511
I am not
madly in love with you.

21:41.511 --> 21:42.722
You're close.
You will be.

21:42.722 --> 21:43.883
I am close
to hating you.

21:43.883 --> 21:45.304
Really? Oh, then we should
just end this right now.

21:45.304 --> 21:47.016
Let's just make out
on the couch.

21:47.016 --> 21:49.138
Sends a clear message,
then everyone knows.

21:49.138 --> 21:51.811
Ooh.
Mm, you're considering it.

21:51.811 --> 21:52.982
You're disgusting.

21:52.982 --> 21:54.434
And yet
you're falling for me.

21:54.434 --> 21:55.935
Shut up.

21:55.935 --> 21:58.988
You are going to say no.

21:58.988 --> 22:03.072
You are going to be very nice,
but you are going to say no.

22:03.072 --> 22:05.204
Got it?

22:05.204 --> 22:06.906
Okay.

22:10.830 --> 22:13.453
Oh, hey, you're here.

22:13.453 --> 22:16.716
Yeah.
I don't know why I came.

22:16.716 --> 22:19.379
He was charged with a felony.
I don't know if you know.

22:19.379 --> 22:21.801
I know.
I was there.

22:24.053 --> 22:26.095
I don't know what's going on
with you guys,

22:26.095 --> 22:28.057
but he's --

22:28.057 --> 22:29.889
Alex is
in a really bad place.

22:29.889 --> 22:31.020
Maybe you could
talk to him.

22:31.020 --> 22:32.061
Why are you
telling me this?

22:32.061 --> 22:33.312
I'm telling you this

22:33.312 --> 22:35.475
because you said
you showed up in court.

22:35.475 --> 22:36.606
I thought you care.

22:36.606 --> 22:38.277
I do care.

22:38.277 --> 22:39.939
Okay,
so then talk to him.

22:39.939 --> 22:42.692
I care about what Alex did
to Andrew.

22:42.692 --> 22:44.484
That's what I care about.

22:50.249 --> 22:53.252
Owen says
they get great morning light.

22:53.252 --> 22:55.455
Light is good.

22:55.455 --> 22:58.297
Yeah, I was thinking, um,
do you want to...
No, we shouldn't.

22:58.297 --> 23:00.500
...double team on that
transplant with me tomorrow?

23:00.500 --> 23:01.921
It should be fun.

23:01.921 --> 23:03.763
Oh, yeah, okay.
We should do that.

23:03.763 --> 23:05.174
-Okay, definitely.
-Mm-hmm.

23:05.174 --> 23:06.966
And then maybe after that,

23:06.966 --> 23:10.720
we could, um, finish up
my resident competency reports.

23:10.720 --> 23:12.391
I'm -- I'm way behind.

23:12.391 --> 23:13.603
Yeah. Okay.

23:13.603 --> 23:15.935
Excellent, definitely.
I can do that, too.

23:15.935 --> 23:17.016
Great, sounds good.

23:17.016 --> 23:18.317
-No problem.
-Great.

23:19.979 --> 23:22.321
I'm gonna go help Amelia.
She can't cook.

23:27.156 --> 23:28.618
[ Sighs ]

23:28.618 --> 23:30.079
-Hey.
-Hey.

23:44.504 --> 23:46.345
-Mommy, I'm scared.
-I know, baby.

23:46.345 --> 23:48.097
What's going on?

23:48.097 --> 23:49.599
His pressure's dropped.
Getting central access.

23:50.720 --> 23:52.101
All right,
get me an art line kit.

23:52.101 --> 23:53.893
It'll be okay, honey.

23:53.893 --> 23:55.314
Mrs. Thompson,
please, step back.

23:55.314 --> 23:56.556
I'm sorry.
He doesn't know you guys.

23:56.556 --> 23:57.687
He needs Dr. Karev.

23:57.687 --> 23:59.438
Where's Dr. Karev?

23:59.438 --> 24:02.732
Yes, uh, can we find out
where Dr. Karev is, please?

24:14.373 --> 24:15.705
Hey.

24:15.705 --> 24:16.956
Hey.

24:18.538 --> 24:20.209
Uh...

24:20.209 --> 24:22.081
You're, uh...

24:22.081 --> 24:24.293
I, uh, didn't know
you'd be here.

24:26.345 --> 24:27.757
How are you?

24:27.757 --> 24:30.850
I don't know
how to answer that.

24:33.893 --> 24:36.095
I'm leaving,
so you can go in.

24:36.095 --> 24:37.977
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

24:37.977 --> 24:40.019
Jo...

24:40.019 --> 24:43.773
I don't want to go in there.
I want to be home with you.

24:43.773 --> 24:44.904
And I messed that up,
and I know that,

24:44.904 --> 24:45.985
and I'm sorry.

24:45.985 --> 24:47.607
You can't just say that.

24:47.607 --> 24:49.278
I mean it,
and I'm gonna keep saying it.

24:49.278 --> 24:51.991
It doesn't fix anything.
Sorry doesn't fix --

24:51.991 --> 24:53.372
Well, what do you
want me to say?

24:53.372 --> 24:55.494
You lash out
and you hurt people,

24:55.494 --> 24:58.377
and then you think you can just
walk it back with "I'm sorry."

24:58.377 --> 25:01.380
I'm not walking anything back.
I might be going to prison.

25:01.380 --> 25:02.501
But you and me --

25:02.501 --> 25:04.924
You and me?
What you and me?

25:04.924 --> 25:07.296
You walked out.
You left.

25:07.296 --> 25:08.467
And I came back.

25:08.467 --> 25:10.129
And then
you called me trash.

25:10.129 --> 25:14.433
And you just --
You said it so easily.

25:14.433 --> 25:16.596
You were trying
to hurt me.

25:18.187 --> 25:20.229
It worked.

25:23.142 --> 25:24.443
Jo!

25:24.443 --> 25:26.736
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

25:36.616 --> 25:37.827
I got your page.

25:37.827 --> 25:39.418
Took you long enough.

25:39.418 --> 25:40.459
What happened?

25:40.459 --> 25:42.752
His appendix ruptured.
He's septic.

25:42.752 --> 25:44.584
All right,
uh, gown and gloves.

25:44.584 --> 25:45.875
Uh, no need.

25:45.875 --> 25:47.797
Dr. Karev
will not be scrubbing in.

25:47.797 --> 25:50.219
You're not touching this boy.
Babcock.

25:50.219 --> 25:51.340
Bailey,
this is my patient.

25:51.340 --> 25:54.343
Not anymore.
You're off this case.

25:54.343 --> 25:56.676
Stapler.

25:56.676 --> 25:58.267
[ Stapler clicks ]

26:03.062 --> 26:05.184
[ Clears throat ]

26:10.489 --> 26:12.531
This is just painful
to watch.

26:12.531 --> 26:13.993
Owen, can I see you?

26:13.993 --> 26:15.615
Sure.

26:15.615 --> 26:19.198
[ Grunts ]

26:19.198 --> 26:20.499
-You're off the hook.
-I told you.

26:20.499 --> 26:22.121
I don't know why you feel
you need to...

26:22.121 --> 26:24.253
I'm a fixer.
I fix things.

26:24.253 --> 26:26.465
I see something sad
and broken,

26:26.465 --> 26:28.838
maybe just a little pathetic,
and I want to fix it.

26:28.838 --> 26:29.879
It's a compulsion.

26:29.879 --> 26:31.510
But we're done here.

26:31.510 --> 26:32.632
Party's over.

26:32.632 --> 26:33.552
No more meddling.

26:33.552 --> 26:34.423
You promise?

26:34.423 --> 26:36.515
Yeah.

26:36.515 --> 26:37.927
Kinda.

26:37.927 --> 26:39.428
Yes.

26:39.428 --> 26:40.479
Good, thank you.

26:40.479 --> 26:42.181
Okay.

26:42.181 --> 26:43.432
[ Sighs ]

26:43.432 --> 26:47.777
Yeah, she just won't
go back to sleep.

26:47.777 --> 26:49.398
Well, let -- let me try.

26:49.398 --> 26:51.490
Can she --
Can she hear me?

26:51.490 --> 26:52.992
-Is the sound okay?
-Yeah, yeah, she can hear you.

26:54.443 --> 26:58.197
♪ Well, I guess
it'd be nice ♪

26:58.197 --> 27:01.330
♪ If I could touch
your body ♪

27:01.330 --> 27:04.704
♪ I know not everybody ♪

27:04.704 --> 27:06.585
♪ Has got a body like you ♪

27:06.585 --> 27:10.509
♪ But I gotta think twice ♪

27:10.509 --> 27:14.303
♪ Before
I give my heart away ♪

27:14.303 --> 27:17.516
♪ And I know
all the games you play ♪

27:17.516 --> 27:20.389
♪ 'Cause I play them, too ♪

27:20.389 --> 27:28.477
♪ Oh, but I need some time off
from that emotion ♪

27:28.477 --> 27:33.442
♪ Time to pick my heart up
off the floor ♪

27:33.442 --> 27:40.449
♪ And when that love comes down
without devotion ♪

27:40.449 --> 27:43.873
♪ Well, it takes
a strong man, baby ♪

27:43.873 --> 27:48.167
♪ But I'm showing you
the door ♪

27:48.167 --> 27:51.460
♪ 'Cause I gotta have faith ♪

27:51.460 --> 27:53.753
♪ I gotta have faith ♪

27:53.753 --> 27:57.096
♪ I gotta have faith,
faith, faith ♪

27:59.058 --> 28:02.261
♪ Baby ♪

28:02.261 --> 28:04.764
♪ I know
you're asking me to stay ♪

28:04.764 --> 28:07.767
♪ So please, please,
please don't go away ♪

28:07.767 --> 28:11.150
♪ You say
I'm giving you the blues ♪

28:11.150 --> 28:13.733
♪ Maybe ♪

28:13.733 --> 28:16.695
♪ You mean every word you say ♪

28:16.695 --> 28:19.408
Oh. I'm so glad
they reached you.

28:19.408 --> 28:20.449
How's Zach?

28:20.449 --> 28:21.911
He's still in surgery.

28:21.911 --> 28:23.873
Why aren't you in there
with him?

28:23.873 --> 28:25.664
Reena --

28:25.664 --> 28:28.207
No, I want you in there.

28:28.207 --> 28:31.881
I'm not
on Zach's case anymore.

28:31.881 --> 28:33.833
I made a mistake.

28:33.833 --> 28:37.006
I missed a sign
that there was an infection.

28:37.006 --> 28:39.048
He's in there
because of you?

28:39.048 --> 28:40.840
I checked his labs
before I left.

28:40.840 --> 28:43.552
You promised me
you'd check him hourly.

28:43.552 --> 28:45.604
Not his labs -- him!

28:45.604 --> 28:47.016
I know.

28:47.016 --> 28:49.058
♪ I gotta have faith ♪

28:49.058 --> 28:50.349
And what about
his kidney?

28:50.349 --> 28:52.111
♪ I gotta have faith ♪

28:52.111 --> 28:55.444
If the infection spreads,
it could affect his transplant.

28:55.444 --> 28:57.616
They're doing
everything they can.

28:57.616 --> 28:59.158
So the next few hours
are crucial.

28:59.158 --> 29:00.489
I'm sorry.

29:00.489 --> 29:01.821
So, he could lose
his kidney.

29:01.821 --> 29:03.282
Yes.

29:03.282 --> 29:05.034
Reena.

29:05.034 --> 29:07.076
Would you please go?

29:07.076 --> 29:09.538
♪ Faith, faith, faith, faith ♪

29:24.383 --> 29:27.266
Where's Alex?
This is his patient.

29:27.266 --> 29:28.647
Not anymore.

29:28.647 --> 29:31.600
What is this I hear
about you threatening DeLuca?

29:31.600 --> 29:35.104
I didn't threaten DeLuca.
I was trying to advise him.

29:35.104 --> 29:36.986
What, you were talking to him
about Karev,

29:36.986 --> 29:39.318
and you know it isn't your place
to discuss that with him.

29:39.318 --> 29:42.031
Bailey, it's Alex.
Yeah, I'm well aware.

29:42.031 --> 29:44.073
I've just spent six hours
in the O.R. because of him.

29:44.073 --> 29:46.245
You are not
Karev's guardian angel.

29:46.245 --> 29:49.078
You are blinded
by this thing.

29:49.078 --> 29:50.579
Look,
I know you want to help.

29:50.579 --> 29:53.332
But there's no need
to go down with him.

29:53.332 --> 29:55.754
I'm his family.
Who else is going to help him?

29:55.754 --> 29:58.297
Did Karev tell you what happened
with this patient tonight?

29:58.297 --> 29:59.919
Huh.
You should ask him.

30:02.551 --> 30:03.472
♪ I gotta have faith ♪

30:11.310 --> 30:13.562
I thought
this little one got to go home.

30:13.562 --> 30:17.526
Uh, yeah, she did.
We're just back visiting Mommy.

30:17.526 --> 30:18.647
May I?
[ Chuckles ]

30:18.647 --> 30:21.941
Sure. There we go.

30:21.941 --> 30:23.402
Yeah.
How's April?

30:23.402 --> 30:25.534
Well, she was up all night
crying.

30:25.534 --> 30:30.079
You know, I took Harriet home,
so she misses her.

30:30.079 --> 30:31.580
She's sad and angry,

30:31.580 --> 30:34.663
and she doesn't really want
any help from me.

30:34.663 --> 30:37.416
Maybe she doesn't want
to ask for help.

30:37.416 --> 30:39.418
I've been there.

30:39.418 --> 30:42.261
Needing prove I could do
something on my own,

30:42.261 --> 30:43.842
determined
not to ask for help.

30:43.842 --> 30:45.464
Yeah, well I can't make her
lean on me.

30:45.464 --> 30:46.675
We're not married anymore.

30:46.675 --> 30:48.557
Now, I thought you were
your mother's son.

30:48.557 --> 30:51.730
You two have a beautiful
baby girl together.

30:51.730 --> 30:53.933
Kepner's family.

30:53.933 --> 30:56.775
Be persistent.

30:56.775 --> 30:58.237
It's what you do
for family.

31:11.951 --> 31:14.163
[ Razor buzzing ]

31:14.163 --> 31:16.335
...which lights up
the borders of the tumor

31:16.335 --> 31:17.917
so that we can get it all.

31:17.917 --> 31:20.799
I know what to expect.
I'm ready.

31:20.799 --> 31:22.171
I can see that.

31:22.171 --> 31:24.343
I can't wait.
Cut open my head.

31:24.343 --> 31:25.554
[ Laughs ]

31:25.554 --> 31:28.307
I get it.
The headaches must be terrible.

31:28.307 --> 31:30.509
No, I know terrible.

31:30.509 --> 31:33.392
I was married to the same man
for over 30 years.

31:33.392 --> 31:34.773
Wasn't the best choice.

31:34.773 --> 31:36.015
Hm.

31:36.015 --> 31:37.776
He was a preacher.

31:37.776 --> 31:39.278
Thought
he could cheat on me

31:39.278 --> 31:41.190
because he had a hotline
to Heaven.

31:41.190 --> 31:44.653
And I just let it happen.

31:44.653 --> 31:46.325
I was a church mouse.

31:46.325 --> 31:48.787
[ Chuckles ] Literally.

31:48.787 --> 31:50.239
I thought of leaving,

31:50.239 --> 31:52.241
but I kept thinking about
how the church would react,

31:52.241 --> 31:54.163
that he'd lose them.

31:54.163 --> 31:57.536
So, I made myself small.

31:57.536 --> 32:01.040
And then I met Wilma --
the tumor.

32:01.040 --> 32:04.173
I knew I had to start
looking out for myself,

32:04.173 --> 32:06.545
so I walked
right out that door

32:06.545 --> 32:10.139
with a tumor the size
of a cantaloupe in my head.

32:10.139 --> 32:12.311
Stronger
because I had to be.

32:12.311 --> 32:14.974
Wilma made you brave.

32:14.974 --> 32:18.517
No, she made me pissed.

32:18.517 --> 32:21.650
Being pissed
made me brave.

32:21.650 --> 32:24.733
Hm.

32:24.733 --> 32:26.655
She shouldn't have taken
that case from you.

32:26.655 --> 32:30.489
I messed up
big time, Mer.

32:30.489 --> 32:31.570
Well, we all mess up.

32:31.570 --> 32:32.951
I mean,
why is everyone around here

32:32.951 --> 32:34.573
acting like they've never
made a mistake before?

32:34.573 --> 32:37.576
Stop.
I torched a kid's kidney,

32:37.576 --> 32:39.418
and he could lose it
because I screwed up.

32:39.418 --> 32:40.379
And I keep screwing up.

32:42.081 --> 32:44.423
Just...open your eyes.

32:44.423 --> 32:47.216
You're backing
the wrong damn horse.

32:47.216 --> 32:49.258
Ben: Dr. Grey.

32:49.258 --> 32:51.260
The Chief wants you
to scrub in on a surgery.

32:51.260 --> 32:53.722
Well, I have
lap chole scheduled, so...

32:53.722 --> 32:55.054
She asked for you.

32:55.054 --> 32:57.686
Uh, the patient has a renal
artery thrombosis post--

32:57.686 --> 32:58.807
Who's the patient, Warren?

33:01.940 --> 33:03.312
Zach Thompson.

33:03.312 --> 33:04.653
There's no blood flowing
to his kidney.

33:04.653 --> 33:05.984
It failed.
We have to remove it.

33:05.984 --> 33:07.606
-Dr. Grey, we should go.
-Okay, okay. Got it.

33:07.606 --> 33:11.820
♪ I'd keep you
under lock and key ♪

33:11.820 --> 33:15.454
♪ It's like you're drippin'
from the ceilings ♪

33:15.454 --> 33:19.168
♪ Wall to wall,
you're all I see ♪

33:19.168 --> 33:25.384
♪ Although everything around me
is screaming otherwise ♪

33:25.384 --> 33:29.468
♪ You're the last thing
on my mind ♪

33:29.468 --> 33:31.970
You asked for me,
Dr. Grey?

33:31.970 --> 33:35.054
Yes, have you ever scrubbed in
on a kidney transplant removal?

33:37.056 --> 33:38.477
It's a yes or no,
DeLuca.

33:38.477 --> 33:40.349
♪ When I go outside ♪
No. No, I haven't.

33:40.349 --> 33:42.401
Well, booty up fast.
We're going in.

33:42.401 --> 33:45.274
♪ Down our beat-up steps ♪

33:45.274 --> 33:51.570
♪ Every crack is just an echo
of the morning when you left ♪

33:51.570 --> 33:54.913
Where's Dr. Alex?
I want Dr. Alex.

33:54.913 --> 33:58.207
Oh, Zach, I'm Dr. Grey.
Dr. Alex can't be here.

33:58.207 --> 34:00.829
But I know he'd want me to
tell you how brave you've been.

34:00.829 --> 34:02.331
But why isn't he here?

34:02.331 --> 34:05.754
♪ ...you're doing fine,
I know it's true ♪

34:05.754 --> 34:07.546
Now, Karev,
you're still off this case.

34:07.546 --> 34:09.428
Does he --
Does he know about his kidney?

34:09.428 --> 34:12.381
His mother wanted us to wait
until after.

34:12.381 --> 34:14.223
All right,
can I see him for a minute?

34:14.223 --> 34:15.884
Just for one minute,
please.

34:15.884 --> 34:18.387
♪ It's like you're drippin'
from the ceilings ♪

34:18.387 --> 34:19.848
♪ Wall to wall,
you're all I see ♪

34:19.848 --> 34:22.020
Dr. Alex,
are you coming with me?

34:22.020 --> 34:23.682
Oh, dude,
I got to stay out here.

34:23.682 --> 34:26.855
Are you gonna sit with my mom?
She's scared.

34:26.855 --> 34:29.648
Are you scared?

34:29.648 --> 34:31.990
Yeah.

34:31.990 --> 34:35.154
Ah, it's a piece of cake.
What do we always say?

34:35.154 --> 34:36.785
Nothing's as bad
as broccoli.

34:36.785 --> 34:38.407
Nothing's as bad
as broccoli.

34:41.200 --> 34:43.962
I'll be here
when you get out, okay?

34:43.962 --> 34:45.464
Okay, let's go.

34:45.464 --> 34:50.088
♪ You're the last thing
on my mind ♪

34:52.010 --> 34:58.517
♪ Although everything around me
is screaming otherwise ♪

34:58.517 --> 35:04.143
♪ You're the last thing
on my mind ♪

35:05.854 --> 35:11.780
♪ You're the last thing
on my mind ♪

35:14.573 --> 35:20.539
♪ Although everything around me
is screaming otherwise ♪
Zach wanted me
to check on you.

35:22.501 --> 35:29.338
♪ I can only find my happiness
in your eyes ♪

35:29.338 --> 35:37.966
♪ Although everything around me
is screaming otherwise ♪

35:37.966 --> 35:40.559
[ Sighs ]
♪ You're the last thing
on my... ♪

35:45.894 --> 35:48.146
[ Rain falling ]

35:50.148 --> 35:52.691
I guess it's time
for you to get going.

36:00.829 --> 36:02.871
[ Baby coos ]

36:05.624 --> 36:06.995
What?

36:06.995 --> 36:09.288
I think you and Harriet
should come live with me

36:09.288 --> 36:11.089
when you get
out of here.

36:11.089 --> 36:13.552
Just until
you've recovered.

36:13.552 --> 36:14.843
No.

36:14.843 --> 36:16.465
April, come on,
you need help.

36:16.465 --> 36:17.886
I know that.

36:17.886 --> 36:19.718
Good, so then why won't you
accept it from me?

36:19.718 --> 36:21.220
Because it's from you.

36:21.220 --> 36:22.931
Come on.

36:22.931 --> 36:24.723
I need boundaries.

36:24.723 --> 36:27.145
And I can
take care of her.

36:27.145 --> 36:28.857
Of course you can,
and you will.

36:28.857 --> 36:30.689
I know
that we need boundaries.

36:30.689 --> 36:32.361
I know that
I'm not your husband.

36:32.361 --> 36:34.573
I also know
that I am Harriet's father.

36:34.573 --> 36:37.656
She needs her mother,
and her mother needs help.

36:39.157 --> 36:41.620
Just think about it.

36:41.620 --> 36:43.622
Okay?

36:43.622 --> 36:45.744
Okay.

36:45.744 --> 36:47.456
She said okay.

36:53.462 --> 36:55.964
Nathan.

36:55.964 --> 36:58.176
Long, long day, huh?

36:58.176 --> 37:00.259
Yeah, it was.
Short ones are boring as hell.

37:00.259 --> 37:01.760
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

37:01.760 --> 37:03.342
Hey.

37:03.342 --> 37:05.013
Do you want to
grab dinner sometime,

37:05.013 --> 37:07.015
like after work,
like away from work,

37:07.015 --> 37:07.976
like a date?

37:07.976 --> 37:08.937
[ Chuckles ]

37:08.937 --> 37:10.479
Like an actual date.

37:12.691 --> 37:14.062
Look,
you're an amazing woman.

37:17.195 --> 37:19.278
Oh.

37:19.278 --> 37:21.490
Okay.

37:21.490 --> 37:24.993
It's just I'm not, um...

37:24.993 --> 37:26.244
I'm not ready to date...

37:26.244 --> 37:27.826
No, right, I...

37:27.826 --> 37:29.828
...anyone, right now.

37:31.580 --> 37:34.333
I-I totally understand.

37:34.333 --> 37:35.504
I'm sorry.

37:35.504 --> 37:37.376
Gosh, no, no.

37:37.376 --> 37:41.219
It's -- Don't --
It's not a big deal.

37:41.219 --> 37:43.221
Have a great night.

37:45.554 --> 37:47.185
You too.

37:57.396 --> 38:00.319
[ Door opens ]

38:00.319 --> 38:01.860
[ Door closes ]

38:01.860 --> 38:04.403
Zach is stable.

38:04.403 --> 38:08.957
We removed a large blood clot
from the artery,

38:08.957 --> 38:10.208
and the kidney
pinked up again.

38:13.251 --> 38:14.873
Thank you.

38:14.873 --> 38:17.676
Hm.

38:17.676 --> 38:20.469
You were the big surprise.

38:20.469 --> 38:23.762
You were most improved.

38:23.762 --> 38:25.424
The person
that beat up DeLuca

38:25.424 --> 38:27.476
is someone I thought
you left behind years ago.

38:27.476 --> 38:29.558
Me too.

38:29.558 --> 38:31.430
I can't in good conscience

38:31.430 --> 38:34.523
let you perform surgery
in this hospital right now.

38:34.523 --> 38:35.644
Hm.

38:35.644 --> 38:37.936
You're a good doctor!

38:37.936 --> 38:39.818
You're compassionate.

38:39.818 --> 38:41.820
And you're good
with people.

38:44.573 --> 38:49.247
You're exactly what we need
right now in the clinic.

38:49.247 --> 38:52.290
A little mole told me
they're short-staffed.

38:52.290 --> 38:53.872
The Denny Duquette Clinic?

38:55.714 --> 38:57.416
Unless you want me
to fire you.

38:59.548 --> 39:02.010
All right, then.

39:02.010 --> 39:04.222
You start tomorrow.

39:04.222 --> 39:05.634
Thanks.

39:12.020 --> 39:14.973
[ Door closes ]

39:14.973 --> 39:16.605
Hey.

39:16.605 --> 39:18.687
This is you and Riggs
at the wedding.

39:18.687 --> 39:20.028
You invited him.

39:20.028 --> 39:21.940
Okay, what happened
to no more meddling?

39:21.940 --> 39:24.362
You married a 12-stepper.
Get used to it.

39:24.362 --> 39:25.574
[ Chuckles ]

39:25.574 --> 39:26.905
Why is this
so important to you?

39:28.156 --> 39:31.660
You guys were like best friends.
You're brothers.

39:33.912 --> 39:35.754
You don't get a lot of those
in your life.

39:37.375 --> 39:39.958
So you have to try.

39:39.958 --> 39:41.710
You're required to try.

39:41.710 --> 39:43.762
I am happy, okay?

39:47.265 --> 39:49.307
You could be happier.

39:49.307 --> 39:52.390
♪♪

39:56.394 --> 39:58.777
[ Electricity buzzing ]

40:08.527 --> 40:13.031
So, do you want me
to stay or go?

40:15.744 --> 40:18.587
'Cause, you know, I mean,
either way...

40:21.209 --> 40:24.463
No, I'm fine.
You can go.

40:30.469 --> 40:33.011
Meredith: We walk through
these doors as interns,

40:33.011 --> 40:36.354
chips on our shoulders,
loners,

40:36.354 --> 40:39.898
lesser rock stars
on the verge of greatness.

40:39.898 --> 40:42.771
I still can't believe
you saved that kidney.

40:42.771 --> 40:44.733
You would have done
the same thing

40:44.733 --> 40:46.154
if you were in there.

40:46.154 --> 40:49.027
Bailey was right.
My head's not in the game.

40:49.027 --> 40:50.869
We're thrown
into the deep end together,

40:50.869 --> 40:52.701
told to save lives together,

40:52.701 --> 40:54.573
to save each other.

40:54.573 --> 40:55.784
We become family.

40:55.784 --> 40:56.955
So get it in the game.

40:56.955 --> 40:58.076
[ Sighs ]

40:58.076 --> 40:59.628
I'm gonna be working
in the clinic for a while.

40:59.628 --> 41:01.710
-That is just --
-It's fine, it's right.

41:01.710 --> 41:03.962
It's not like
I didn't do it to myself.

41:06.424 --> 41:08.176
I slept with Riggs.

41:08.176 --> 41:09.588
Okay.

41:09.588 --> 41:10.929
In the parking lot.

41:10.929 --> 41:12.801
In my car.

41:12.801 --> 41:14.352
In the car
you drove me home in?

41:14.352 --> 41:15.594
It's bad.

41:15.594 --> 41:16.765
[ Door opens ]
It was bad?

41:16.765 --> 41:18.186
No, it's bad because --

41:18.186 --> 41:19.518
[ Door closes ]
Maggie: Hey.

41:19.518 --> 41:20.689
What are we drinking?

41:26.234 --> 41:27.866
Slow down.

41:27.866 --> 41:30.609
My God,
that was humiliating.

41:30.609 --> 41:33.071
It was worse than being dumped
by DeLuca.

41:33.071 --> 41:34.743
And now he knows
how much I like him.

41:34.743 --> 41:36.615
Why am I crying?

41:36.615 --> 41:39.417
At some guy who said no?

41:39.417 --> 41:41.710
-[ Sighs ]
-Who said what?

41:41.710 --> 41:43.672
You live here now,
so you're gonna hear things.

41:43.672 --> 41:45.253
[ Clears throat ]
It's Riggs.

41:45.253 --> 41:46.334
I asked him out.

41:46.334 --> 41:47.796
And he said no.

41:47.796 --> 41:49.838
So fast

41:49.838 --> 41:51.930
You know what?
Forget him.

41:51.930 --> 41:54.012
It's really time
to move on.

41:54.012 --> 41:55.223
Okay.

41:55.223 --> 41:56.975
Look on the bright side.

41:56.975 --> 42:00.689
Yeah, he did say
he wasn't dating right now.

42:00.689 --> 42:01.940
And even when
you really screw up...

42:01.940 --> 42:04.192
